full_text:
I use the same thing I use with the randomly tuned boxes, a white 
generator, amplifier, and filter. I just added the filter so I can 
adjust the data rate if needed. I used discrete component schmit 
trigger, inverter, and an AND gate for data control. I still remain 
kinda doubtful of this project without a processor of somekind to 
actually control the Speakjet, but --how do ya know it won&#39;t work if 
ya don&#39;t try it? I think I&#39;ll end up using something like a Basic 
Stamp to randomly feed the numbers for allophone access to the 
Speakjet. 

 I joined the Speakjet yahoo group, but so for I think the 
science/techno dorks are ignoring my request for guidence.

 Frank-S

